The paper discusses compressed sensing applied to inverse problems, which is a topic commonly studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design of optimal sampling strategies and efficient sparsity bases, which are topics that fall under Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Machine Learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a numerical experiment, which is a common feature of papers in the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
